There's a Mr. Bronx
Charlie to see you.

24:35.980 --> 24:39.097
I'll be right in. Show them
into the conservatory.

24:39.260 --> 24:39.851
Very good, sir.

24:40.500 --> 24:42.491
Aren't you gonna play no more?

24:42.780 --> 24:45.055
Later, my rose. Later.

24:47.700 --> 24:52.615
<i>Velia, oh Velia...</i>

24:52.860 --> 24:56.455
<i>the witch of the wood...</i>

24:58.980 --> 25:06.853
<i>would I not die for
you if I could.</i>

25:08.380 --> 25:12.692
<i>Velia, oh Velia...</i>

25:13.020 --> 25:14.738
- Next!
- Very nice.

25:14.900 --> 25:17.334
Lovely. Next.
Get off the stage!

25:17.860 --> 25:19.179
Don't give up your day job.

25:20.140 --> 25:22.335
I didn't figure
on this many people.

25:22.500 --> 25:24.536
They all look like
jugglers and magicians.

25:25.140 --> 25:27.779
Don't worry. You got no
competition. You'll walk it.

25:27.940 --> 25:28.850
Hurry up.

25:29.820 --> 25:31.333
Evening, ladies and gentlemen.

25:31.860 --> 25:35.136
I'm proud to be here.
In fact, I'm lucky to be here.

25:35.300 --> 25:37.131
Because as I was coming here...

25:37.740 --> 25:39.651
- How do I look?
- Fine.

25:40.060 --> 25:42.449
- I look terrible.
- Believe me, you look swell.

25:42.860 --> 25:44.054
- Honest?
- Honest.

25:44.220 --> 25:46.814
- Cross your heart?
- Cross my heart. Beautiful.

25:49.420 --> 25:50.216
Next.

25:51.980 --> 25:54.619
<i>Once I built a railroad...</i>

25:54.860 --> 25:57.090
Not that old chestnut.

25:57.420 --> 25:58.569
Get him off. Next.

25:58.980 --> 26:01.096
Good evening.

26:01.620 --> 26:04.737
Suppose you're
wondering why we're here.

26:04.900 --> 26:05.491
You bet.

26:05.980 --> 26:06.776
Next.

26:06.940 --> 26:07.850
Not one rabbit...

26:08.980 --> 26:10.049
not two rabbits...

26:10.860 --> 26:12.339
but three rabbits.

26:12.580 --> 26:14.172
Next, next.

26:16.220 --> 26:17.016
Next.

26:29.060 --> 26:30.015
Yeah, great. Okay.

26:30.380 --> 26:32.450
Next one there, please.

26:32.660 --> 26:33.456
Give me your things.

26:33.620 --> 26:35.451
Come on, come on.

26:45.500 --> 26:47.092
Blousey Brown, singer.

26:50.140 --> 26:51.050
Oh, nice face.

26:51.300 --> 26:54.019
Great face, could
do a lot with that.

26:56.580 --> 26:57.217
Oscar.

26:57.540 --> 26:58.177
Oscar.

26:58.620 --> 26:59.257
Oscar.

26:59.500 --> 27:02.810
I'm back. I'll give
you one more chance.

27:03.020 --> 27:05.170
Lena, you've come back to me.

27:05.380 --> 27:07.052
I'll give you one more chance.

27:07.420 --> 27:10.457
Otherwise, I'm out for
good. Out, out, out!

27:10.660 --> 27:12.616
I won't be humiliated.

27:12.780 --> 27:16.455
I'm the star and I
should be treated like one.

27:16.940 --> 27:18.419
Hit it, Joe.

27:23.380 --> 27:25.848
<i>Show business,
it's in my veins...</i>

27:26.140 --> 27:28.415
<i>gotta keep singing
that old refrain...</i>

27:28.580 --> 27:31.094
<i>I thrill to all those tunes
that make me wanna dance...</i>

27:31.260 --> 27:33.012
Cheer up. There's
a million other jobs.

27:33.180 --> 27:36.013
Sure, standing on the
corner asking for dimes.

27:36.180 --> 27:39.297
It's only a matter of time.

27:39.740 --> 27:43.494
I've walked the streets for
months, and the only fancy steps...

27:43.660 --> 27:45.696
I've been doing is avoiding
the rent collector.

27:46.140 --> 27:47.892
Takes time to be a movie star.

27:48.060 --> 27:49.288
We could come back tomorrow.

27:49.580 --> 27:53.016
Come back tomorrow? I spend
my whole life doing that.

27:53.180 --> 27:55.057
Knock it off. Cool down.

27:55.220 --> 27:56.414
I will not cool down.

27:56.580 --> 27:57.569
Don't be stupid.

27:58.060 --> 27:59.698
Will you be quiet up there?

27:59.900 --> 28:01.253
I'm rehearsing.

28:03.060 --> 28:04.891
- I'm sorry.
- Don't worry.

28:06.220 --> 28:08.176
There's always Fat Sam's place.

28:08.340 --> 28:10.092
- He won't see me.
- I'll talk to him.

28:10.260 --> 28:12.535
- You know him?
- Know him? We're like that.

28:12.820 --> 28:13.650
You're good friends?

28:14.180 --> 28:17.252
No, but when I see him I cross my
fingers that he won't hit me.

28:17.540 --> 28:19.337
Come on, let's get out of here.

28:20.060 --> 28:21.732
You're too good for this show.

28:21.900 --> 28:24.414
- Why don't we try Fat Sam's?
- Yeah.

28:24.980 --> 28:25.935
<i>You gotta be kidding...</i>

28:26.420 --> 28:31.494
<i>that show business is my business...</i>

28:40.660 --> 28:42.412
- Hi, boys.
- Hi, boss.

28:42.900 --> 28:44.856
Relax, relax, will you?

28:48.660 --> 28:52.699
I'd like to take the opportunity
to thank you for your work.

28:53.300 --> 28:56.019
Everything's gone so well.

28:56.180 --> 28:57.090
Thanks, boss.

28:57.420 --> 28:58.330
Thanks, boss.

28:59.140 --> 29:01.290
Fat Sam must've had quite a shock.

29:01.460 --> 29:02.779
- Quite a shock.
- Thanks, boss.

29:03.900 --> 29:05.652
- Thanks, boss.
- Thanks.

29:06.380 --> 29:06.971
Thanks, boss.

29:07.660 --> 29:08.331
Laughing boy.

29:09.580 --> 29:13.937
Yonkers. Shoulders.
Bronx Charlie. Benny Lee.

29:14.820 --> 29:17.288
Any moment now Fat Sam will be...

29:17.460 --> 29:18.734
crawling on his knees to me.

29:18.900 --> 29:19.730
On his knees.

29:19.900 --> 29:22.619
- Where's my flower, boss?
- Yes...

29:22.780 --> 29:25.852
soon all Fat Sam will have
is the suit he stands up in...

29:26.020 --> 29:27.055
and a suitcase full of memories.

29:29.100 --> 29:30.249
I don't have a flower, boss.

29:47.940 --> 29:48.577
What did I do?

29:48.860 --> 29:50.896
You googed, Doodle.
You dropped the gun.

29:51.540 --> 29:53.258
And I don't allow mistakes.

29:53.420 --> 29:55.012
'Cause they put us in the caboose.

29:55.900 --> 29:58.255
- And Sing Sing ain't my style.
- No, boss.

29:58.420 --> 30:00.251
Not that. Anything but that.

30:00.740 --> 30:02.890
I didn't mean to drop it.
It slipped outta my hands.

30:03.300 --> 30:05.211
Button your lip.
You're all washed up.

30:05.540 --> 30:07.690
- Give a guy a break.
- Get him!

30:14.220 --> 30:17.417
Now listen to what I
say, and listen good.

30:18.260 --> 30:20.137
There's only room for one
Mr. Big in this town.

30:20.700 --> 30:22.338
And that's me, Dandy Dan.

30:23.020 --> 30:25.853
The time has come for
us to play our next card.

30:26.540 --> 30:29.054
Believe me, Fat Sam
and his dumb bums...

30:29.220 --> 30:30.892
ain't gonna stand in our way.

30:31.300 --> 30:32.733
<i>We could've been anything...</i>

30:32.900 --> 30:34.572
<i>that we wanted to be.</i>

30:35.660 --> 30:38.538
<i>But don't it make your heart glad...</i>

30:39.980 --> 30:43.529
<i>that we take pride in it...</i>

30:44.300 --> 30:47.133
<i>we became the best at being bad.</i>

30:48.540 --> 30:51.976
<i>We could've been
anything we wanted to be...</i>

30:52.980 --> 30:55.369
<i>with all the talent we had.</i>

30:57.140 --> 31:00.769
<i>No doubt about it,
we whine and we pout it...</i>

31:01.540 --> 31:02.893
<i>we're the very best at being...</i>

31:03.060 --> 31:05.051
<i>bad guys.</i>

31:05.460 --> 31:07.132
<i>We're rotten to the core...</i>

31:07.780 --> 31:11.693
<i>congratulations,
no one likes you anymore...</i>

31:12.220 --> 31:13.812
<i>bad guys...</i>

31:14.100 --> 31:15.613
<i>we're the very worst.</i>

31:16.540 --> 31:18.258
<i>Each of us contemptible...</i>

31:18.420 --> 31:20.297
<i>we're criticized and cursed...</i>

31:21.020 --> 31:22.135
<i>we've made the big-time...</i>

31:22.300 --> 31:24.450
<i>malicious and mad...</i>

31:25.300 --> 31:28.178
<i>we're the very best at being bad.</i>

31:28.780 --> 31:30.133
<i>Look at me, I'm dancin'.</i>

31:31.660 --> 31:34.936
<i>We could've been anything
we wanted to be...</i>

31:36.020 --> 31:38.454
<i>we took the easy way out...</i>

31:40.340 --> 31:43.855
<i>with a little training,
we've mastered complaining...</i>

31:44.340 --> 31:46.410
<i>made us seem unnecessary...</i>

31:46.580 --> 31:48.650
<i>we're so rude, it's scary...</i>

31:48.860 --> 31:52.057
<i>We could've been anything
we wanted to be...</i>

31:53.140 --> 31:55.290
<i>with all the talent we had...</i>

31:57.380 --> 31:58.733
<i>with a little practice</i>

31:58.980 --> 32:00.811
<i>we made every black list...</i>

32:01.700 --> 32:02.416
<i>we're the very best...</i>

32:02.580 --> 32:04.411
<i>at being bad...</i>

32:05.860 --> 32:06.690
<i>we're the very best...</i>

32:06.860 --> 32:08.498
<i>at being bad.</i>

32:08.660 --> 32:09.456
<i>Where you shovin' me?</i>

32:10.140 --> 32:12.973
<i>We're the very best at being bad.</i>

32:29.380 --> 32:31.940
What are you doing?

32:32.260 --> 32:34.057
Get in here, you bunch
of peanut brains.

32:34.540 --> 32:36.178
Get in here, you dummies.

32:36.340 --> 32:38.729
We got business
to do. Move it!

32:48.140 --> 32:49.539
Come on, get in here.

32:50.300 --> 32:51.494
We got business to do.

32:51.660 --> 32:53.173
We can't waste
all this time.

32:54.300 --> 32:54.891
Right.

32:55.260 --> 32:56.170
Let's get down to it.

32:57.140 --> 32:59.449
Don't do that, Snake Eyes.
It's thinking time.

33:00.580 --> 33:01.979
And don't do that, Knuckles.

33:02.460 --> 33:03.210
Sure thing, boss.

33:03.540 --> 33:04.893
Let's start at the beginning.

33:05.660 --> 33:08.220
We're being outsmarted
by that lounge lizard.

33:08.380 --> 33:10.450
And we're gonna get back on top.

33:10.620 --> 33:11.894
Back on top.

33:12.060 --> 33:14.255
We'll kick that drugstore cowboy...

33:14.420 --> 33:15.978
- into line.
- You bet, boss.

33:16.380 --> 33:19.895
We've been a little slow off
the mark, but dumb bums we ain't.

33:20.060 --> 33:22.369
No, dumb bums we ain't.

33:23.300 --> 33:24.619
Hand me a pie.

33:28.620 --> 33:31.180
- Louie, over there in the corner.
- Me, boss?

33:32.340 --> 33:33.090
Why me?

33:33.500 --> 33:34.489
Louie, into the corner.

33:35.020 --> 33:35.896
What did I do?

33:36.260 --> 33:37.010
Nothing, Louie.

33:38.340 --> 33:40.137
You see? Missed.

33:40.820 --> 33:42.458
Okay, Lou. You can sit down.

33:43.020 --> 33:45.659
Even a dumb bum like
Louie is too quick for us.

33:46.460 --> 33:49.418
That's our trouble.
We're behind the times.

33:49.700 --> 33:51.019
I don't get it.

33:51.180 --> 33:54.252
We'll never get back on top
with this kind of hardware.

33:54.420 --> 33:55.648
It's old-fashioned.

33:56.100 --> 33:59.490
In short, we gotta
get that gun.

34:03.740 --> 34:05.458
<i>- Hello.
- Want some information?</i>

34:05.620 --> 34:06.939
<i>- Start gabbin'...
- It's about the splurge gun.</i>

34:07.100 --> 34:09.091
<i>It's at the Hung Fu
Shin laundry company.</i>

34:09.260 --> 34:10.898
Yeah. Okay. Thanks.

34:14.219 --> 34:17.018
We've had a little break.

34:18.100 --> 34:19.976
Who knows the Hung Fu
Shin laundry company?

34:21.300 --> 34:25.771
My friend tells me that's
where they stash the guns.

34:26.780 --> 34:27.576
Get moving!

34:28.820 --> 34:30.856
Not you, Knuckles.
Stay here with me.

34:31.020 --> 34:31.735
Sure, boss.

35:43.380 --> 35:44.972
Hello. What?

35:47.020 --> 35:49.739
I don't believe it.
The whole gang?

35:50.860 --> 35:51.531
Everybody?

35:57.740 --> 36:00.698
That leaves you and
me. We're on our own.

36:01.140 --> 36:02.368
What we gonna do?

36:03.100 --> 36:05.295
Don't do that! How many
times I got to tell you?

36:06.500 --> 36:09.139
Do nothing. Act like
everything was normal.

36:11.620 --> 36:14.498
- What does that mean?
- You can't speak Italian?

36:15.020 --> 36:16.135
No, boss, I'm Jewish.

36:16.500 --> 36:17.933
Then read the translation!

36:42.660 --> 36:44.139
- Hey, Fizzy.
- Hey, Bugsy.

36:44.660 --> 36:46.855
- Still practicing?
- Still practicing.

36:49.420 --> 36:51.456
Suddenly everybody wants
to be in show business.

36:52.580 --> 36:55.538
Hi. Tallulah. I've
come to see Fat Sam.

36:55.980 --> 36:57.857
- Is he in?
- No, he's busy.

36:58.700 --> 37:00.258
- Hi, Bugsy.
- Hi.

37:01.500 --> 37:03.058
Have a drink while you wait.

37:05.980 --> 37:07.095
Yeah, why not?

37:09.580 --> 37:11.332
Go feed the ducks, will you?

37:11.500 --> 37:12.933
Oh, Tallulah.

37:13.100 --> 37:14.294
I said, beat it.

37:22.620 --> 37:24.212
Long time no see.

37:24.780 --> 37:27.533
- You know how it is.
- Yeah.

37:29.820 --> 37:31.811
You used to come see me every night.

37:31.980 --> 37:34.494
- I've been busy.
- Busy doing what?

37:35.180 --> 37:36.249
This and that.

37:40.340 --> 37:42.615
Fizzy, cut the ivory
and hit the shoe leather.

37:44.660 --> 37:45.376
Yes, ma'am.

37:52.220 --> 37:53.369
You're aces, Bugsy.

37:55.340 --> 37:56.819
I always found you special.

37:57.260 --> 37:59.410
Careful, you're racing my mother.

37:59.580 --> 38:02.219
Come on, give a girl a break.

38:02.380 --> 38:04.018
Sure you've got the right fella?

38:04.180 --> 38:06.694
- You're not like those other saps.
- No?

38:07.220 --> 38:07.811
No.

38:09.260 --> 38:11.216
You've got lovely brown eyes.

38:11.580 --> 38:13.889
They'll be black eyes
if Fat Sam catches us.

38:15.540 --> 38:18.134
- How about smearing my lipstick?
- Careful.

38:18.380 --> 38:21.452
If you come any closer,
I'll have to call my lawyer.

38:23.060 --> 38:23.651
So call him.

38:33.020 --> 38:33.816
Blousey.

38:35.580 --> 38:36.217
Blousey.

38:37.620 --> 38:38.609
Blousey.

38:44.860 --> 38:46.896
It's the broad about the audition.

38:47.380 --> 38:49.018
He's busy. Come back tomorrow.

38:49.740 --> 38:50.536
No, no, no.

38:51.340 --> 38:54.059
Hey, honey. I'm all ears.
Be with you in a minute.

38:55.940 --> 38:58.659
Carry on as normal.
Don't let 'em know we're beat.

38:58.820 --> 39:00.538
- Business as usual.
- Right.

39:00.700 --> 39:02.292
- Calm and collected.
- Right.

39:02.460 --> 39:04.690
So they don't know we're
scared. I mean, concerned.

39:05.260 --> 39:05.851
Sure, boss.

39:19.500 --> 39:22.173
<i>I'm feeling fine...</i>

39:22.900 --> 39:25.494
<i>filled with emotions...</i>

39:26.180 --> 39:28.853
<i>stronger than wine...</i>

39:29.180 --> 39:31.535
<i>they give me the notion...</i>

39:31.780 --> 39:34.658
<i>that this strange new feeling...</i>

39:34.940 --> 39:39.536
<i>is something that
you're feeling too.</i>

39:45.100 --> 39:46.818
<i>Matter of fact...</i>

39:48.140 --> 39:50.893
<i>I'm forced to admit it...</i>

39:51.380 --> 39:53.371
<i>caught in the act...</i>

39:54.580 --> 39:56.457
<i>and maybe we've hit it...</i>

39:57.020 --> 40:00.057
<i>this strange new feeling...</i>

40:00.340 --> 40:03.332
<i>is something you're feeling...</i>

40:03.500 --> 40:05.570
Okay, honey. That's enough.

40:06.700 --> 40:10.215
A little contemporary for
me, but very nice. You're hired.

40:21.380 --> 40:24.053
That was great. That
really was. Terrific.

40:27.540 --> 40:28.336
Blousey.

40:29.100 --> 40:30.499
Come back, will you?

40:31.500 --> 40:33.092
What's the use?

40:33.740 --> 40:34.650
I've got to go.

40:42.180 --> 40:43.010
Blousey.

40:44.380 --> 40:46.769
Where is she? Blousey.

41:14.580 --> 41:16.172
Show's going swell.

41:16.500 --> 41:18.138
Just the way I want it to be.

41:21.260 --> 41:23.251
Same number of
drinks, same everything.

41:24.100 --> 41:26.091
They mustn't know
they've got us on the run.

41:28.580 --> 41:29.979
Here, I wanna show you something.

41:31.820 --> 41:34.778
I've sent for someone to
help us out of our predicament.

41:35.220 --> 41:37.336
No ten-cent dummy. A specialist.

41:37.940 --> 41:38.736
A doctor?

41:39.260 --> 41:41.728
Not a doctor, a hoodlum.

41:42.860 --> 41:44.737
I thought we were hoodlums.

41:45.220 --> 41:47.859
Not a dumb bum. This
guy is the real McCoy.

41:48.340 --> 41:49.739
Not Looney Bergonzi!

41:49.900 --> 41:50.969
<i>The Looney Bergonzi?</i>

41:51.180 --> 41:54.775
The very same, mad
as a hatter, Bergonzi.

41:55.340 --> 41:57.934
Best man in Chicago.
Here's what we do.

41:58.580 --> 42:01.936
We meet Dandy Dan.
Looney hides in the back seat.

42:02.180 --> 42:03.659
- You drive.
- Right.

42:06.420 --> 42:08.331
- But I don't drive.
- You what?

42:10.020 --> 42:10.896
You don't drive?

42:11.820 --> 42:14.254
Then we get ourselves a driver.

42:22.180 --> 42:24.171
- Hi, Bugsy.
- Is Blousey there?

42:24.340 --> 42:26.296
- She won't see you.
- Tell her I'm sick.

42:26.500 --> 42:28.491
- You're sick?
- Sick of waiting.

42:32.740 --> 42:33.570
Beat it.

42:33.980 --> 42:35.652
Give a guy a break.

42:36.380 --> 42:37.415
I brought you some flowers.

42:37.860 --> 42:39.054
I'll see Tallulah gets them.

42:39.260 --> 42:41.410
Quit being smart. They're for you.

42:41.660 --> 42:42.649
Five minutes, girls.

42:42.900 --> 42:44.856
- I have to go.
- I was thinking of getting a job.

42:45.420 --> 42:47.251
You don't get paid for
standing in bread lines.

42:47.500 --> 42:51.732
A legit job. We could save
enough money to go to Hollywood.

42:51.940 --> 42:53.658
Believe it when I see it.

42:56.460 --> 42:58.815
- Bugsy, you drive?
- Sure, why?

42:59.140 --> 43:02.416
- Like to earn some green stuff?
- Long as it ain't cabbages.

43:02.820 --> 43:05.175
Step inside. I got
a proposition for you.

43:06.820 --> 43:07.969
Flowers? For me?

43:08.300 --> 43:10.097
How nice.

43:10.460 --> 43:12.257
Put these in water.

43:22.620 --> 43:23.416
Hello?

43:25.940 --> 43:29.330
Who shall I say is
calling? One moment.

43:58.380 --> 44:00.735
- Hello.
- Dandy Dan, is that you?

44:01.460 --> 44:04.020
- This is Dandy Dan speaking.
- I wanna arrange a meeting.

44:04.460 --> 44:07.611
- Sure. Where?
- Outta town.

44:07.820 --> 44:10.459
Agreed. Just you and a driver.

44:10.820 --> 44:14.096
- When?
- Monday. 11 A.M..

44:14.460 --> 44:15.449
Right, I'll be there.

44:16.180 --> 44:17.818
<i>Got him, the knuckle.</i>

44:18.260 --> 44:19.773
<i>Got him, the salami.</i>

44:19.940 --> 44:21.896
Let's go and enjoy the show.

44:31.780 --> 44:33.850
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

44:34.140 --> 44:35.892
<i>my first rule of thumb...</i>

44:36.420 --> 44:40.732
<i>I don't say where I'm going,
or where I'm coming from.</i>

44:41.100 --> 44:45.378
<i>I try to leave a little
reputation behind me...</i>

44:46.140 --> 44:50.179
<i>so if you really need to,
you'll know how to find me.</i>

44:59.340 --> 45:01.410
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

45:01.700 --> 45:03.452
<i>I live till I die...</i>

45:03.980 --> 45:05.254
<i>I'll take what you give me...</i>

45:05.420 --> 45:08.218
<i>and I won't ask why.</i>

45:08.620 --> 45:12.010
<i>I've made a lot of friends
in exotic places...</i>

45:13.220 --> 45:14.289
<i>I don't remember names...</i>

45:14.460 --> 45:17.770
<i>but I remember faces.</i>

45:27.020 --> 45:34.017
<i>Lonely, you don't
have to be lonely...</i>

45:36.300 --> 45:42.250
<i>come see Tallulah, we can
chase your troubles away.</i>

45:44.580 --> 45:47.890
<i>If you're lonely...</i>

45:48.060 --> 45:52.338
<i>you don't have to be lonely.</i>

45:53.740 --> 45:58.211
<i>When they talk to Tallulah,
you know what they say...</i>

45:58.980 --> 46:03.053
<i>no one south of heaven's
gonna treat you finer...</i>

46:03.380 --> 46:07.771
<i>Tallulah had her training
in North Carolina.</i>

46:16.860 --> 46:19.055
<i>My name is Tallulah...</i>

46:19.220 --> 46:20.892
<i>and soon I'll be gone...</i>

46:21.540 --> 46:25.579
<i>an open invitation
is the road I travel on.</i>

46:26.100 --> 46:30.412
<i>I never say goodbye
because the words upset me.</i>

46:30.740 --> 46:32.856
<i>You may forgive my going...</i>

46:33.020 --> 46:35.534
<i>but you won't forget me.</i>

46:44.460 --> 46:47.020
<i>Lonely...</i>

46:47.180 --> 46:51.537
<i>you don't have to be lonely...</i>

46:53.660 --> 46:59.337
<i>come see Tallulah, we can
chase your troubles away.</i>

47:01.940 --> 47:05.137
<i>If you're lonely...</i>

47:05.300 --> 47:09.896
<i>you don't have to be lonely...</i>

47:11.260 --> 47:15.458
<i>when they talk about Tallulah,
you know what they say...</i>

47:16.220 --> 47:20.338
<i>no one south of heaven's
gonna treat you finer...</i>

47:20.620 --> 47:25.296
<i>Tallulah had her training
in North Carolina.</i>

48:07.940 --> 48:08.531
They're coming.

48:08.980 --> 48:10.015
Looney, keep your head down.

48:31.980 --> 48:33.129
What can I do for you?

48:33.540 --> 48:35.576
How about some straight talk?

48:35.820 --> 48:36.730
Suits me.

48:36.900 --> 48:39.539
- You've been taking liberties.
- I've been taking what's mine.

48:39.700 --> 48:41.975
- Trouble is, it belongs to me.
- Too bad.

48:42.620 --> 48:45.737
I'm sure we can talk
it over. I'm a businessman.

48:46.060 --> 48:47.937
Yeah, a dime-a-dozen gangster.

48:48.180 --> 48:50.296
Button your lip.
Don't talk dirty to me.

48:50.460 --> 48:52.894
I don't like your
mouth. Have some respect.

48:53.260 --> 48:55.569
You'd slit your own
throat for two bits.

48:55.740 --> 48:57.571
Keep your wisecracks.

48:58.700 --> 48:59.689
Keep talking.

49:00.100 --> 49:01.931
I have my position to think of.

49:02.100 --> 49:04.216
Right now it's not worth a nickel.

49:04.380 --> 49:06.257
You're a dirty rat, Dan.

49:06.420 --> 49:08.536
You've been watching
too many movies.

49:09.380 --> 49:10.529
Okay, Looney, let him have it.

49:10.780 --> 49:12.418
Charlie, Yonkers,
it's a double-cross.

49:13.180 --> 49:14.932
Okay, freeze.

49:23.260 --> 49:23.851
Looney.

49:26.620 --> 49:28.178
What's the matter with you?

49:38.020 --> 49:38.975
Hey, you guys.

49:39.140 --> 49:39.970
Over here!

49:40.180 --> 49:41.169
Over here!

49:44.100 --> 49:45.738
Come back, dummies!
They're getting away.

49:46.180 --> 49:47.295
Come back here.

49:47.860 --> 49:51.569
Come on, step on it.

49:53.980 --> 49:55.049
Come on, let's go.

50:06.140 --> 50:07.334
We're going to lose them.

50:07.780 --> 50:08.929
Drive faster.

50:21.940 --> 50:22.929
Dan, you're a rat!

50:26.460 --> 50:27.779
You're a dirty rat!

50:28.100 --> 50:29.613
Come on, they're gonna get us.

50:38.580 --> 50:39.808
Hold tight, Mr. Stacetto.

51:04.140 --> 51:04.777
Come on, Malone.

51:06.260 --> 51:08.979
You're a dirty
double-crossing rat!

51:11.500 --> 51:12.091
Look out.

51:15.180 --> 51:15.771
Don't stop!

51:15.940 --> 51:16.656
There's a bridge!

51:16.860 --> 51:17.895
Put the brakes on!

51:21.060 --> 51:23.210
We lost them.

51:30.700 --> 51:34.056
Go and cluck somewhere else.

51:35.460 --> 51:38.179
Here. Get yourself a new suit.

51:39.100 --> 51:40.579
Get rid of the sack you're wearing.

51:41.020 --> 51:43.488
Thank you, Mr. Stacetto.

51:43.660 --> 51:45.491
Here's my tailor's card.

51:45.900 --> 51:47.856
You ain't got to
pay for six months.

51:48.460 --> 51:49.370
Thank you very much.

51:49.540 --> 51:52.816
Think nothing
of it. Let's go.

52:01.300 --> 52:03.291
What do you think?
Don't I look cute?

52:04.300 --> 52:04.937
I don't know.

52:05.220 --> 52:06.448
Come on, Dotty,
what do you think?

52:07.260 --> 52:09.057
I think the color's wrong.

52:09.260 --> 52:10.773
What are you talking about?

52:10.940 --> 52:12.692
Purple's my color.

52:13.220 --> 52:14.369
Don't I always wear purple?

52:14.540 --> 52:15.768
It matches your nose.

52:16.020 --> 52:16.975
Maybe it's the length.

52:17.380 --> 52:20.497
It's the latest length. Look!

52:20.660 --> 52:24.175
Maybe the frills stick out
too much. Like your ears.

52:24.940 --> 52:27.215
Frills are in. Look at
this photo of Lena Marelli.

52:27.420 --> 52:29.331
Lena Marelli is
not Bangles Dobell.

52:29.500 --> 52:31.695
You think it'd
look better on you?

52:31.860 --> 52:32.975
It'd look better on a horse.

52:33.380 --> 52:36.736
Jealous. Can I help it if my
looks are ahead of their time?

52:37.340 --> 52:38.216
What?

52:38.540 --> 52:39.290
Full of character.

52:39.500 --> 52:40.091
Kind of earthy.

52:40.260 --> 52:41.659
Like a bucket of mud.

52:42.260 --> 52:44.376
You creep. Get lost!

52:49.020 --> 52:51.409
How about you? Do you
think I look terrible?

52:54.100 --> 52:56.773
Do I look cute or terrible?

53:00.340 --> 53:00.931
Honestly?

53:01.740 --> 53:05.096
Bangles Dobell, you look terrible.

53:07.460 --> 53:08.370
What are you looking at?

53:09.340 --> 53:09.977
Nothing.

53:46.820 --> 53:47.457
<i>Blousey.</i>

53:54.700 --> 53:55.371
Blousey.

54:03.100 --> 54:03.771
Blousey.

54:04.780 --> 54:06.054
It's for you. It's Bugsy.

54:09.820 --> 54:10.775
Give him my love.

54:12.700 --> 54:13.291
Thanks.

54:14.060 --> 54:14.651
Hello.

54:15.020 --> 54:16.692
Blousey, it's Bugsy.

54:16.860 --> 54:17.451
Where are you?

54:17.620 --> 54:21.533
Around. I can't talk,
but I just made 200 bucks.

54:21.820 --> 54:23.139
You printed it yourself?

54:23.460 --> 54:24.609
No, I earned it.

54:24.860 --> 54:25.497
Doing what?

54:25.820 --> 54:26.616
Oh, this and that.

54:27.060 --> 54:28.288
Hang on a minute.

54:28.780 --> 54:29.769
I can't hear you.

54:29.940 --> 54:31.498
There's a train going by.

54:32.820 --> 54:33.730
Who gave you the money?

54:34.900 --> 54:35.491
Fat Sam.

54:35.780 --> 54:37.418
He gave you 200 dollars?

54:37.780 --> 54:39.657
And the loan of his
sedan for the afternoon.

54:39.980 --> 54:41.413
He loaned you his sedan?

54:41.900 --> 54:43.572
I don't believe it.
You're putting me on.

54:46.500 --> 54:47.296
I believe you.

54:49.940 --> 54:51.214
<i>He's a sinner...</i>

54:52.340 --> 54:54.092
<i>candy-coated...</i>

54:55.020 --> 54:59.093
<i>he always seems to be alone...</i>

55:00.620 --> 55:06.172
<i>but they love him,
Bugsy Malone.</i>

55:10.180 --> 55:11.659
<i>A city slicker...</i>

55:12.900 --> 55:15.653
<i>he can charm you with a smile...</i>

55:16.100 --> 55:18.694
<i>a style all his own...</i>

55:20.140 --> 55:23.291
<i>everybody loves that man...</i>

55:23.860 --> 55:26.818
<i>Bugsy Malone.</i>

55:33.300 --> 55:35.097
<i>Hard-headed Bugsy...</i>

55:35.260 --> 55:36.693
<i>makes his mind up...</i>

55:38.700 --> 55:41.692
<i>don't mess with Bugsy,
or you'll wind up...</i>

55:42.860 --> 55:46.773
<i>wishing you'd left him alone.</i>

55:47.940 --> 55:50.773
<i>He's a man, a mountain,
he's a rolling stone...</i>

55:53.140 --> 55:54.858
<i>and when he leaves you...</i>

55:55.740 --> 55:57.298
<i>sad and lonely...</i>

55:57.460 --> 55:59.655
<i>cry, I couldn't say.</i>

56:00.260 --> 56:01.773
<i>But it's known...</i>

56:02.900 --> 56:06.370
<i>that everybody
wants that man...</i>

56:06.780 --> 56:09.248
<i>Bugsy Malone.</i>

56:20.380 --> 56:21.972
Mustard with onions or ketchup?

56:22.140 --> 56:22.890
Mustard with onions.

56:23.500 --> 56:24.728
Oh, and this, too.

56:25.140 --> 56:27.290
- What's this?
- A present.

56:27.460 --> 56:28.688
- Open it up.
- You got to be kidding.

56:29.060 --> 56:30.049
I don't kid around.

56:30.580 --> 56:32.775
It's beautiful.

56:33.340 --> 56:33.931
Nice, huh?

56:34.100 --> 56:34.930
What is it?

56:35.300 --> 56:37.052
What is it? A viewer.

56:37.460 --> 56:38.973
Look through here.

56:39.420 --> 56:41.058
Pictures of Hollywood stars.

56:41.220 --> 56:42.050
Bugsy...

56:42.300 --> 56:44.530
it's fantastic. It really is.

56:45.300 --> 56:47.018
If only I could get to Hollywood.

56:47.260 --> 56:47.897
You can.

56:48.340 --> 56:48.977
Sure.

56:49.140 --> 56:50.209
I know, in the front row...

56:50.380 --> 56:51.290
of the Roxy Theatre...

56:51.460 --> 56:52.290
on East 38th Street.

56:52.460 --> 56:54.212
No, really get to Hollywood.

56:54.660 --> 56:55.490
Keep talking.

56:55.660 --> 56:56.888
1.80 for the viewer, right?

56:57.620 --> 56:58.939
10 cents for the hot dogs.

56:59.860 --> 57:02.374
Leaves 198 dollars for...

57:02.580 --> 57:03.171
Surprise me.

57:03.340 --> 57:04.773
- Two tickets.
- Two tickets?

57:05.180 --> 57:06.215
How many tickets you need?

57:06.580 --> 57:07.615
Two tickets to the ball game?

57:07.820 --> 57:09.139
To Hollywood, dummy.

57:09.780 --> 57:12.248
This can't be true.
Are we really going?

57:12.420 --> 57:13.409
Knock it off.

57:13.860 --> 57:14.690
You're putting me on.

57:15.140 --> 57:15.970
It's the honest truth.

57:16.540 --> 57:17.609
I'm picking them up tomorrow.

57:17.980 --> 57:20.414
Now I better get
Fat Sam's car back.

57:20.700 --> 57:21.928
Or I'm not going anywhere.

58:01.060 --> 58:01.936
Is anyone in there?

58:05.220 --> 58:05.811
Hello?

58:07.420 --> 58:08.011
Are you hurt?

58:11.500 --> 58:12.774
Help! Somebody
help me, please!

58:14.940 --> 58:15.895
Somebody, please!

58:16.060 --> 58:16.890
Somebody help!

58:18.260 --> 58:19.295
Help me, please!

58:33.020 --> 58:34.248
They take your money?

58:38.100 --> 58:39.852
Yeah. Nearly 200 dollars.

58:40.460 --> 58:42.769
Thanks anyway for helping me.

58:43.180 --> 58:43.851
It was nothing.

58:44.700 --> 58:46.497
- You must be a boxer, right?
- No.

58:47.060 --> 58:48.618
- You're not?
- No.

58:48.940 --> 58:50.419
Best punching I ever saw.

58:50.860 --> 58:52.418
- Ever been coached?
- No.

58:53.020 --> 58:54.817
- Ever thought of taking it up?
- No.

58:55.500 --> 58:57.456
Why not? You could be a champion.

58:58.060 --> 59:00.699
- Never had the chance.
- I know who could help you.

59:00.860 --> 59:02.816
- You know Cagey Joe?
- No.

59:03.340 --> 59:05.615
- You must know Slugger's Gym?
- No.

59:06.300 --> 59:08.860
- You don't know much, do you?
- Nope.

59:09.580 --> 59:10.569
What's your name?

59:10.780 --> 59:12.532
Smith, Leroy Smith.

59:12.980 --> 59:15.016
I'm Bugsy Malone. Put it there.

59:15.660 --> 59:16.854
You got yourself a manager.

59:18.180 --> 59:20.455
- Know the first thing I'm gonna do?
- No.

59:20.620 --> 59:23.134
Treat you to one heck of a meal.

59:23.340 --> 59:26.138
- Thought they took all your dough.
- Who needs money?

01:00:26.700 --> 01:00:28.816
Look at this, O'Dreary.

01:00:31.460 --> 01:00:33.530
You cracked it this time, Captain.

01:00:33.980 --> 01:00:35.618
Get the plaster.
We'll take a mold.

01:00:35.940 --> 01:00:37.168
Come on, get the plaster.

01:00:38.140 --> 01:00:41.849
Careful. Up a bit.

01:00:42.220 --> 01:00:46.293
Left a bit.

01:00:46.620 --> 01:00:47.336
Come on, hurry up.

01:00:47.620 --> 01:00:50.134
Hold it straight. Be careful.

01:00:57.100 --> 01:00:58.294
You idiots!

01:01:01.860 --> 01:01:02.849
Hello. What?

01:01:03.140 --> 01:01:06.496
They got the still.
The whole lot's gone.

01:01:06.860 --> 01:01:10.216
Not the sarsaparilla racket,
too. Get round here now.

01:01:10.540 --> 01:01:11.973
- I can't, boss.
- Why not?

01:01:12.500 --> 01:01:13.376
I'm all tied up.

01:01:13.700 --> 01:01:15.930
I don't care if you're
busy. Get here right away.

01:01:17.060 --> 01:01:21.053
Careful, you idiots.

01:01:21.500 --> 01:01:22.330
O'Dreary.

01:01:22.700 --> 01:01:23.291
Don't worry...

01:01:23.460 --> 01:01:26.054
we'll break you out
at headquarters.

01:01:37.820 --> 01:01:40.778
- Hi, Bugsy. How you been?
- Swell, Cagey Joe.

01:01:41.260 --> 01:01:43.979
I'd like you to meet the
next heavyweight champion.

01:01:44.140 --> 01:01:45.653
Leroy, meet Cagey Joe.

01:01:45.900 --> 01:01:48.175
Cagey Joe, this is Leroy Smith.

01:01:48.580 --> 01:01:51.094
- Ever been in the ring before?
- No.

01:01:51.780 --> 01:01:53.736
- So you wanna be a fighter?
- No.

01:01:53.900 --> 01:01:56.095
Sure he does. He's a natural.

01:01:56.540 --> 01:01:57.450
Look at those fists.

01:01:57.740 --> 01:01:58.855
Did you ever see such fists?

01:01:59.420 --> 01:02:00.011
Hit it, Leroy.

01:02:02.860 --> 01:02:04.498
You see? A born champion.

01:02:05.100 --> 01:02:06.010
What's your name again?

01:02:06.340 --> 01:02:08.058
Smith. Leroy Smith.

01:02:08.340 --> 01:02:10.729
With your help...

01:02:11.020 --> 01:02:12.419
he could be champion in no time.

01:02:22.220 --> 01:02:24.131
<i>So you wanna be a boxer...</i>

01:02:24.540 --> 01:02:25.859
<i>in the golden ring.</i>

01:02:26.780 --> 01:02:28.736
<i>Can you punch like a train?</i>

01:02:29.020 --> 01:02:30.135
<i>Tell me just one thing...</i>

01:02:30.740 --> 01:02:33.698
<i>can you move like a
hummingbird's wing?</i>

01:02:34.060 --> 01:02:35.015
<i>Oh, that's fast!</i>

01:02:35.180 --> 01:02:38.092
<i>Can you bob, can you weave?</i>

01:02:38.940 --> 01:02:40.737
<i>Well, you might as well quit...</i>

01:02:41.180 --> 01:02:42.374
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

01:02:44.580 --> 01:02:47.777
<i>So you wanna be a boxer,
can you pass the test?</i>

01:02:48.940 --> 01:02:52.137
<i>I can tell if you got it,
I've trained the best.</i>

01:02:53.380 --> 01:02:57.009
<i>When you work and sweat
like a buzz saw...</i>

01:02:57.180 --> 01:02:58.408
<i>and you near lose your mind...</i>

01:02:58.580 --> 01:03:00.332
<i>when you find out your
boy has a glass jaw.</i>

01:03:01.140 --> 01:03:02.334
<i>So you might as well quit...</i>

01:03:03.260 --> 01:03:04.488
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

01:03:06.380 --> 01:03:08.257
<i>Put him in the ring,
look at what you've found...</i>

01:03:08.500 --> 01:03:09.489
<i>we can use the fun...</i>

01:03:09.660 --> 01:03:10.376
<i>pushing him around.</i>

01:03:10.540 --> 01:03:12.019
<i>We'll show him the ropes...</i>

01:03:12.700 --> 01:03:14.338
<i>and destroy his hopes...</i>

01:03:15.220 --> 01:03:16.130
<i>put him in the ring...</i>

01:03:16.300 --> 01:03:18.416
<i>let him feel the sting...</i>

01:03:18.580 --> 01:03:19.251
<i>we can make him dance...</i>

01:03:19.420 --> 01:03:20.853
<i>we'll pound him to bits...</i>

01:03:21.500 --> 01:03:24.810
<i>then he'll call it quits.</i>

01:03:28.180 --> 01:03:29.977
Come on, Leroy.

01:03:33.300 --> 01:03:36.690
<i>So you wanna be a boxer,
wanna be the champ...</i>

01:03:37.820 --> 01:03:41.369
<i>there's a golden boy inside
you, not a punchy tramp...</i>

01:03:41.740 --> 01:03:44.618
<i>if you listen and you learn,
there's an honor you can earn...</i>

01:03:46.100 --> 01:03:49.092
<i>when you see the crown,
you're a king, not a clown.</i>

01:03:49.980 --> 01:03:51.208
<i>But you might as well quit...</i>

01:03:52.140 --> 01:03:53.368
<i>if you haven't got it.</i>

01:03:55.220 --> 01:03:57.131
<i>Put him in the ring,
something new to punch...</i>

01:03:57.420 --> 01:03:59.251
<i>let me have a swing...</i>

01:03:59.420 --> 01:04:00.773
<i>then we'll go to lunch...</i>

01:04:01.580 --> 01:04:03.059
<i>then he'll get the drift.</i>

01:04:04.020 --> 01:04:05.897
<i>Put him in the ring,
chicken Ã  la carte...</i>

01:04:06.260 --> 01:04:08.057
<i>let me have a wing,
tearing him apart.</i>

01:04:08.220 --> 01:04:09.619
<i>The chicken will crow...</i>

01:04:10.220 --> 01:04:13.451
<i>let me have him, Joe.</i>

01:04:31.500 --> 01:04:32.137
He's got it.

01:04:33.380 --> 01:04:35.450
You sure this is going to work?

01:04:35.740 --> 01:04:38.300
Sure. Looks like a splurge gun.

01:04:38.660 --> 01:04:39.251
Doesn't it?

01:04:39.500 --> 01:04:43.288
- Sort of.
- Nonsense.

01:04:43.580 --> 01:04:46.777
Anything Dandy Dan can
do, I can do better.

01:04:47.940 --> 01:04:48.850
Are you ready?

01:04:49.220 --> 01:04:49.811
Ready.

01:04:51.820 --> 01:04:52.855
Don't do that!

01:04:53.020 --> 01:04:53.896
Sorry, boss.

01:04:54.260 --> 01:04:55.170
All right, take aim.

01:04:58.100 --> 01:04:58.691
Ready.

01:05:03.100 --> 01:05:03.691
Get set.

01:05:06.140 --> 01:05:06.731
Fire.

01:05:11.620 --> 01:05:12.211
Missed!

01:05:12.860 --> 01:05:14.532
Back to the drawing board.

01:05:16.740 --> 01:05:17.456
Knuckles!

01:05:18.100 --> 01:05:19.055
Knuckles, speak to me.

01:05:19.220 --> 01:05:19.811
Knuckles.

01:05:32.260 --> 01:05:34.728
It's all your fault, hear me?

01:05:55.060 --> 01:05:55.651
Hello?

01:05:57.540 --> 01:05:59.496
Not the grocery racket, too?

01:06:01.220 --> 01:06:01.811
Yeah.

01:06:03.100 --> 01:06:06.934
That's the whole empire
